snippet.textDisplay:
Still remember that day in 2013. I just joined college then. One of my cousins, told me about this song. I had a phone which didn't have enough space to store this video. I bought a memory card just to save this masterpiece. What a lovely song!

Feeling good to see Rajasthani music getting its much deserved place. Thanks to Amit Trivedi, Mame Khan, and whole team.

Still my favo Mame Khan song 😍
No matter how many times I hear this, even if I don’t understand the language…
It gives an instant happy feeling, joy and urge to dance 💃.  And I do so love your voice 
Although this is so not “European” or “our” kind of music, I really do love it and never get tired of listening to all colours of your wonderful voice and folk sound and instruments
